<chapter title="Installing Solitaire" file="Install">

<cite>Solitaire</cite> can be run off a hard disc or floppy disc.

To install <cite>Solitaire</cite> on a hard disc, copy the <file>!Solitaire</file> application to a suitable place on your disc.

</chapter>




<chapter title="Using Solitaire" file="Use">

<cite>Solitaire</cite> is a desktop version of the traditional game. Load it on to the icon bar in the usual way and click <mouse>select</mouse> on the icon to open the game window.

To play, drag the counters around with <mouse>select</mouse>. A counter can be moved horizontally or vertically into an empty space by jumping over exactly one filled space; the aim is to clear the board down to one remaining counter.

To re-fill the board, click <mouse>menu</mouse> over the main window and select <menu>New Board</menu>. The <menu>Solid Drags</menu> option in the iconbar menu alternates between dragging sprites and dotted boxes.

</chapter>




